{"actor":"jawnbrown","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-05-22T13:58:16Z","event_type":"claimed","id":"c95e2dfb-d24f-4004-bc6f-c5acfa02a568","issue_id":"revpref-uko","new_value":"{\"assignee\":\"jawnbrown\",\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"revpref-uko\",\"title\":\"Implement Windows installed-app inventory importer\",\"description\":\"Turn the Windows PowerShell collector sketch into a supported import flow that emits normalized app records from registry uninstall keys, MSIX packages, startup commands, and optional WinGet metadata.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"Running the importer on Windows creates normalized app records with stable IDs, name, vendor, size, startup entries, and uninstall handoff where available.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"feature\",\"owner\":\"86195310+jawnbrown@users.noreply.github.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T20:24:55Z\",\"created_by\":\"jawnbrown\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T20:24:55Z\"}"}
{"actor":"jawnbrown","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-05-22T14:10:14Z","event_type":"closed","id":"04e8f6df-074e-40f5-9f60-426e7429d8ec","issue_id":"revpref-uko","new_value":"Implemented read-only Windows inventory collection via npm run collect:windows. Collector now emits normalized registry app records, startup entries, uninstall handoff metadata, optional MSIX records, and optional WinGet package ID enrichment. Verified on local Windows machine: 1008 registry records, 23 startup-linked records, 93 WinGet matches; --include-msix produced 1169 records. npm test passes.","old_value":""}
